<HEADLINE> DPRK, South Korean Troops Clash on MDL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Military forces of the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and South Korea
clashed on the Military Demarcation Line (MDL) today, with both
sides accusing each other of serious provocation.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK's Korean Central News Agency pyongyang reported that
South Korean troops "fired recoilles guns and 12.7 mm
machine-guns, about 3,060 shells and bullets in all, at (the
DPRK's) people's army soldiers on routine patrol duty near the
military demarcation line in the central sector of the front this
morning."
</P>
<P>
"The firing left some of the people's army soldiers seriouly
injured and destroyed the outpost buildings," it said.
</P>
<P>
"The people's army soldiers were compelled to take self-
defensive measures under the grave situation. The two sides,
therefore, went into fierce armed conflict on the MDL," the news
agency said.
</P>
<P>
"The reckless armed provocation of the puppets is part of the
traitor kim young sam's deliberate and premeditated moves to find
a way out of the most serious ruling crisis in a shocking
incident," it added.
</P>
<P>
In Seoul, South Korean military officials said the DPRK's
forces fired artillery shells at a Southern guard post, in what
was one of the worst border clashes in recent years.
</P>
<P>
"We strongly warn that we will never tolerate any provocation
in the future," Lieutenant-General Joung Young-moo said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
Joung said the incident began when seven DPRK soldiers crossed
the MDL that runs through the middle of the four-km wide
Demilitarized Zone, which separates the Korean peninsula under a
truce agreement signed at the end of the 1950-53 Korean War.
</P>
<P>
South Korean troops fired shots in the air after broadcasting
warning messages on loudspeakers. DPRK forces responded with
about 80 rounds of rifle fire at two guard posts, which returned a
similar burst of fire.
</P>
<P>
Yeo Sook-dong, chief spokesman for South Korea's Joint Chiefs
of Staff, told reporters that DPRK forces then fired 10 artillery
rounds that landed near a DMZ guard post on the southern side.
</P>
<P>
South Korean troops responded with one round from a recoilless
rifle. The shooting lasted for less than an hour and ended just
before noon (0300 GMT) after the Southern side broadcast a
ceasefire proposal.
</P>
<P>
No southern casualties were reported in the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
