<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Indigenous Businesses Urged to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- A senior Zimbabwean official today urged
indigenous business groups to participate in the government's
proposed five-year program to provide water to rural communities
constituting 70 percent of the population.
</P>
<P>
Lands and Water Resources Deputy Minister Cain Mathema said
the 227.3 million U.S. Dollars program presented vast
opportunities for emerging business people to form companies that
could build dams, drill boreholes and erect reticulation systems
to improve the supply of water.
</P>
