<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- More than 5,000 delegates, with at
least 1,000 from the United States, are expected to participate
in the fourth African African-American summit scheduled for July
20 to 26 in Harare, the summit organizer said here today.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the summit, the organizer will concurrently
host a four-day summit trade investment exposition from July 22
to 25, which will seek to connect the world market with African
businesses and introduce local entrepreneurs to the world market.
</P>
<P>
The organizer said, "this represents a unique opportunity for
small, medium and large business organizations to identify trade
and investment opportunities in Africa and interact with
high-level American decision makers and businessmen."
</P>
<P>
The summit, with the theme of "economic development,
investment, and education in Africa", is aimed at bringing
together delegates from around the world to discuss and
articulate solutions to the advancement of Africa, added the
organizer.
</P>
<P>
Although 25 heads of state from various countries are expected
to take part in the biennial event, only five have so far
confirmed their participation. 
