<HEADLINE> Khamenei Urges to Fight Corruption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ali Khamenei
today called on the nation to fight against ever worsening
violation of public security.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with commanders of the Law Enforcement Forces and
officials of the social welfare organizations, Khamenei stressed
"security should govern every aspect of public life."
</P>
<P>
He called for strong measures against those violating public
security.
</P>
<P>
"The Law Enforcement Forces should strictly observe morals and
ethics and should bear themselves with trust and dignity in
discharging their duties," he was quoted by the official news
agency IRNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed, "those elements violating the spirit and
letter of the law from inside the police force itself should be
severely dealt with."
</P>
<P>
The Ayatollah urged law enforcement officials to expose any
wrongdoings within the forces and not to be lenient to any failure
on those in performing their duties.
</P>
<P>
The statement by Khamenei indicates that the top Iranian
leaders have already been aware of public complaints about
violations of the Law Enforcement Forces, such as abuse of rights,
extortion for money and other kinds of corruption.
</P>
<P>
"The Law Enforcement Forces should be changed into a body that
the Islamic system requires," the supreme leader said.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also called on the legislative body and the judiciary
to deal with those who have accumulated unauthorized assets,
adding "we will not allow a new class to take shape such as those
who misuse the public funds for their personal purposes."
</P>
<P>
"Those committed to Islam and the Islamic revolution will not
allow such wrongdoings or the emergence of a new class made
wealthy with unauthorized assets through misuse of public funds,"
he warned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
