<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investments Show Confidence In Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Five Hong Kong investments last
year confirmed the high degree of confidence in the UK from the
now special administrative region of China.
</P>
<P>
Details released today by the British government's Invest in
Britain Bureau (IBB) show Hong Kong firms invested around 80
million US dollars in the UK during the 1996/97 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
During the year the United Nations Conference on Trade and
Development reported that direct investment by Hong Kong and other
Asian countries in Europe reached an average 860 million US
dollars between 1992 and 1994, with 40 percent of the European
Union's entire stock from that source going to the UK.
</P>
<P>
Britain also continued to attract over 40 percent of the EU's
American investment and was the leading recipient of cross-border
investment among member countries as well.
</P>
<P>
In all, the total value of foreign owned investment stock in
the UK is estimated to have reached nearly 256 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Sales of British businesses to overseas investors were
estimated to have exceeded the total for all other EU combined.
Some 60 percent of new investments were expansions by existing
investors.
</P>
<P>
The new Labor government is strongly committed to encouraging
further investment and maintaining stable conditions through
flexibility and competitiveness. 
</P>
</TEXT>
