<HEADLINE> Israel Accuses Palestinian Policemen Of Terrorist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli Defense Minister,
Yitzhak Mordechai, today again accused three Palestinian policemen
of involvement in what he called a terrorist gang, according
to a report of the state-run Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Mordechai said that Israel is very
concerned about the fact that Palestinian policemen took part
in a terrorist mission. He was referring to three Palestinian
policemen who were arrested by Israeli security forces earlier
this week.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Defense Forces (IDF) claimed that the three
were on their way to carry out an attack on the Jewish
settlement of Har Bracha near Nablus.
</P>
<P>
But the Palestinian Police denied that the three policemen
were on their way to attack Israelis. A senior Palestinian
police official said the three, one of whom was wounded
during the arrest and hospitalized at Tel Hashomer, were in
pursuit of a "suspicious vehicle."
</P>
<P>
"It is too dangerous. It is something that can damage the
whole peace process with the Palestinians," Mordechai warned.
</P>
<P>
He said that it is necessary for (PLO) Chairman (Yasser)
Arafat and the Palestinian National Authority to understand that
it is the highest mistake that has been made by the Palestinian
police to use their weapons and power against the Israeli people.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai said that their weapons should be used against
violence and terrorism and establish order and peace in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Israel was furious when Palestinian police used their weapons
to fight Israeli soldiers in September last year. A total of
15 Israeli soldiers were killed during the bloody clashes, which
happened due to the opening by Israel of a tunnel close to
Temple Mount, the Moslem holy site, in the Old City of
East Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
