<HEADLINE> Cameroun Adopts Budget for 1997/19987 Fiscal Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Cameroun's parliament adopted its
state budget for the fiscal year 1997/1998 on Tuesday, with the
total amount standing at 1,256 billion CFA Francs (about 2.16
billion U.S. Dollars), "Cameroun Tribune" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The current budget which is to be promulgated into law by
President Paul Biya has witnessed an increase of 13 percent as
compared to that of last year.
</P>
<P>
The lion's share of the current budget goes to the Ministry of
National Education with a package of 84 billion CFA Francs or
144.8 million Dollars, whereas the Economic and Social Council
has the lowest budgetary allocation of 336 million CFA Francs
(approximately 579,000 Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new budget aims to increase public finances, mobilizing
external finance and reviving national economy.
</P>
<P>
The budget was tabled at the National Assembly by Cameroun's
Prime Minister Peter Mafany Musonge on July 7. 
</P>
