<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, July 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's Vice-President Kocheril Raman Narayanan
was elected new president of the country today.
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. Space shuttle Columbia with its crew of
seven returned to Earth today with a bounty of laboratory research
on fire, metals and plants.
</P>
<P>
NASA's oldest shuttle glided through a clear, flushed sky and
touched down just after sunrise at Kennedy Space Center in Florida
following a 16-day journey, according to media reports.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW, -- Nine people were killed, dozens injured and five
were still trapped under rubble today after a military school
dormitory in western Siberia collapsed, reports said.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people, most of them cadets, were in the three-story
building of the Tomsk Military Communications School in the city
of Tomsk when the roof collapsed five minutes before the wake-up
call at 6 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60 people were taken to hospital and 10 were in critical
condition. Five were still trapped several hours after the
accident and rescue workers had to clear the rubble with their
bare hands.
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A Fokker-27 plane of Indonesia's Sempati Airlines
with 43 passengers and five crew members on board crashed today in
West Java, killing 23 people.
</P>
<P>
The plane crashed at Mergahayu Permai housing complex, Bandung
regency.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated plane crashed not long after it left Bandara
Husein Sastranegera, Bandung, at 11:45 a.m. for Jakarta, capital
of Indonesia, a spokesman of the Husein Sastranegara Airport said
in Bandung this afternoon, reports reaching here said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
