<HEADLINE> Masters' Individual Painting Exhibitions Open in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 paintings by three
Chinese masters were put on display at separate exhibitions here
today in this largest Chinese city.
</P>
<P>
The work of Qi Baishi (1864-1957) displays a simple and
unaffected style, and was regarded as a leading proponent of
traditional Chinese painting; Liu Haisu (1896-1994) was the
founder of modern fine arts education in China; and Lin Fengmian
(1900-1991) was famous for his work combining traditional Chinese
style with Western style.
</P>
<P>
Some of the work exhibited is on public display for the first
time.
</P>
<P>
The three are being exhibited at the Art Gallery of Liu Haisu,
and are part of the "China Art Exhibition" sponsored by the
Ministry of Culture. 
</P>
