<BODY>
<HEADLINE> West China Development Network Center Set Up in Yinchuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The headquarters of a development
network for west China was established today in Yinchuan, the
capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the network, which was founded by economic
development pilot areas, is to develop new industries, expand
co-operation in the West, and build a "western science and
technology corridor".
</P>
<P>
Another function is to try to increase co-operation between
western and eastern parts of China and to bring in more foreign
funds.
</P>
<P>
The West includes Chongqing Municipality, formerly in Sichuan
province; Shaanxi, Gansu, Sichuan, Qinghai, and Guizhou provinces;
and the autonomous regions of Ningxia, Xinjiang, Tibet, and
Guangxi. It covers an area of about 57 million sq kilometers, or
58.4 percent of the China's total area, and has more than 40
million ethnic minority people, or 55 percent of the country's
total. It shares 13,000 km of border line with 14 other countries.
</P>
<P>
The network is expected to help high-tech industries in west
China and hopefully help turn the area from a poverty-stricken area
into a prosperous one, according to Xu Guanhua, vice-minister in
charge of the State Science and Technology Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
