</P>
<P>
-- Federal investigators who completed the most comprehensive
audit of Medicare to date said the Government overpaid hospitals,
doctors and other health-care providers last year by 23 billion
dollars, or 14 percent of all the money spent in the traditional
Medicare program. An official said there was no way to tell how
much of the overpayment resulted from fraud.
