whether new admission policies at the University of California,
the first school to ban affirmative action in selecting students,
violate federal civil rights law.
</P>
<P>
USA Today:
</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton and the Federal Trade Commission Wednesday
delivered a double-barreled attack against the exploitation of
children on the Internet. 
