<HEADLINE> 31 killed In Southwest China Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-one people have been
reportedly killed and five injured in a landslide in southwest
China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The landslide was caused by heavy rainfalls that have pounded
the province for the past three days.
</P>
<P>
It occurred in the early hours of the morning of July 15 in
Panxian County in the southwest part of the province. The heavy
slide also destroyed a dozen houses.
</P>
<P>
The local government immediately sent work teams to the site of
the accident and a round-the-clock effort has been underway to
look for survivors and aid the victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
