<HEADLINE> Japan Grants 12 Million U.S. Dollars to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The government of Japan has
agreed to grant an assistance of some 706 million rupees (about 12
million U.S. dollars) to Nepal for increasing food production and
construction of primary schools.
</P>
<P>
Two separate notes to this effect were exchanged at the Nepali
Finance Ministry today between the two governments, the official
RSS news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Of the amount, 422 million rupees (about 7 million U.S.
dollars) will be utilized for purchasing fertilizer, agricultural
machinery and equipment in order to increase food production.
</P>
<P>
And the rest will be for providing materials and equipment for
the construction of primary schools, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Japan is the biggest donor to Nepal among the Nepal Aid Group,
which consists of 23 countries and international institutions.
</P>
</TEXT>
