<HEADLINE> Nine Killed, Five Trapped as Russian Barracks Collapse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed, dozens
injured and five were still trapped under rubble today after a
military school dormitory in western Siberia collapsed, reports
said.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people, most of them cadets, were in the three-story
building of the Tomsk Military Communications School in the city
of Tomsk when the roof collapsed five minutes before the wake-up
call at 6 a.m. local time.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60 people were taken to hospital and 10 were in critical
condition. Five were still trapped several hours after the
accident and rescue workers had to clear the rubble with their
bare hands. Reports said their chances of survival were slim.
</P>
<P>
The building was old and had not been repaired since the early
1950s when it was converted from a monastery into a dormitory. A
third story was later constructed on top of the two original
levels, Itar-Tass reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
