<DOCNO> XIE19970717.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Contract Responsibility System to Be Maintained, Chen Junsheng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, July 17 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Chen Junsheng
called on rural officials to stick to household-based contract
responsibility system.
</P>
<P>
During his inspection in northeast China's Heilongjiang
province between July 8-17, Chen said that at present any attempt
to replace the system with other systems should be prevented.
</P>
<P>
"Anything that will damage the farmers' interest should be
banned, " Chen said.
</P>
<P>
The household-based contract responsibility system, initiated
in east China's Anhui province in 1979, was spread all over the
country in two years. It was a break from the state-ownership and
helped boost the country's annual grain output from 300 billion kg
in late 1970s to 490 billion kg in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
