<BODY>
<HEADLINE> eds Tree Seeds Help China's Afforestation Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The current yearly output of tree
seeds in China is 19 million kg, double the 1990 figure, basically
meeting the nation's afforestation needs, according to the
Ministry of Forestry.
</P>
<P>
China's afforestation drive depends largely on the supply of
tree seeds and young seedlings. According to the source, about 82
percent of tree seeds and 85 percent of seedlings are suitable for
planting.
</P>
<P>
In the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, which is famous for
its melons and other fruits, six new apricot strains have
reportedly increased apricot output four to five times.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Forestry said that since 1993, China has been
successful in improving more than 1,000 various tree species.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry has also issued 31 statements of standards for
tree seed and seedling production.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Guangyao, Vice-Minister of Forestry, said that in the near
future China will build another 30 seed centers and 50 nurseries
for seedlings.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest Ministry of Forestry plan, by the year
2000, China's forest coverage will reach 15.5 percent, and its
urban green coverage will reach 30 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
