<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Profile: Narayanan, India's Newly Elected President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- India's newly elected President
Kocheril Raman Narayanan was born on February 4, 1921 in Uzhavoor
village of Kerala state in far southwestern India. He was once
barred from school for not being able to pay his fees.
</P>
<P>
After graduating from university, he took up a job in the
central secretariat as an assistant. But after a few weeks, he
resigned and worked for the weekly "Commerce and Industry".
</P>
<P>
Then he went to Britain to continue his study. When he came
back, he has been a pen-pusher, teacher, journalist, diplomat,
vice chancellor, union minister and vice president.
</P>
<P>
Narayanan served in Indian embassies in Vietnam and Australia
and as ambassador in Thailand, Turkey and China. He retired from
the foreign service in 1978 and entered politics later. After
being elected a member of Parliament, he was appointed by Rajiv
Gandhi as minister of state for planning.
</P>
<P>
In 1992, he was chosen as a candidate for vice presidency and
was elected almost unanimously with just one vote cast against
him.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
