<HEADLINE> 60 Rebels Killed in North Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 17 (Xinhua) -- At least 60 Tamil rebels were
killed Wednesday when they confronted government troops engaged in
Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain Victory) in Northern province, a
military spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, B. Sarath Munasinghe, said at a news briefing
here that the troops have recovered 17 rebel bodies and a large
amount of arms and ammunition following an encounter with a large
group of rebel cadres, about three kilometers northwest of
Nedunderni on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the soldiers inflicted heavy casualties on the rebels,
killing at least 60 rebels and injuring 100 others.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 16 soldiers were also killed in the attack,
according to informed sources here.
</P>
<P>
Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain Victory) was launched on May 13
by government troops.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a war for a separate Tamil
state in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
