<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaria Reappears in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaria, which was wiped out in
Albania 33 years ago, has reappeared in the country following the
diagnosis of an Albanian sailor as carrying the disease, media
reports said here today.
</P>
<P>
The Tirana Hospital for Infectious Diseases was quoted as
saying that the sailor contracted malaria during his stay in
Tanzania. All other sailors on the same ship are being given
medical check-ups.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Ministry of Health and the Environment has
informed the World Health Organization (WHO) and requested drugs
to prevent and cure this "imported" malaria.
</P>
<P>
Cholera and osteomyelitis, which had not been reported in
Albania for many years, have also reappeared mainly due to
pollution and poor medical care, the media said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
