<DOCNO> XIE19970717.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Circular On Purchasing Grain At Protective Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Grain Reserve
Administration has issued a circular calling on local grain
purchasing departments to buy grain from farmers at protective
grain prices and without limits.
</P>
<P>
Open-ended grain purchasing at protective prices is a key
government measure to protect farmers' benefits, increase their
income, and protect farmers' enthusiasm in grain production, the
circular explains.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 900 million farmers in China, and the
income from grain production is a major means of improving their
lives and of increasing production.
</P>
<P>
If grain production worsens, the general economic development
and social stability will be affected, it pointed out, adding
that this decision by the central government shows the stability
of the state's agricultural policy, which will benefit farmers for
a long time to come.
</P>
<P>
As a major part of the grain circulation system, state-run
grain departments should strictly adhere to the central
government's grain-purchasing policy, and buy farmers' extra grain
without IOUs, the circular said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
