<HEADLINE> World's Third Largest Mobile Phone User </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Chen Jianshe, a worker from a
Nanjing transportation company, became China's 10 millionth mobile
phone buyer today.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications gave the lucky man
a certificate and an extra mobile phone as a prize.
</P>
<P>
China now ranks third in the world in the number of people
using mobile phones, after the United States and Japan.
</P>
<P>
China's mobile phone industry didn't take shape until 1987. It
now has networks connecting all cities and some villages, and the
number of customers has been growing 100 percent annually on
average, sources from the Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications
say. 
</P>
