<HEADLINE> Moorcroft Named British Athletics Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Former men's 5,000 meters world
record holder David Moorcroft was appointed chief executive of the
British Athletic Federation on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Moorcroft, 44, retired from the track four years ago and still
holds the European 5,000 meters record.
</P>
<P>
He succeeds former international Peter Radford who quit in
April after three years in charge.
</P>
<P>
Moorcroft will take up his post on October 1. 
