<HEADLINE> China to Random Charge on Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Communist Party
Central Committee and the State Council have issued a circular
calling for further effort to stop random charges levied against
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It says that the problem has not been properly solved and that
the burden on enterprises jeopardizes the relationship between the
Party and the people.
</P>
<P>
Any random fees, collections, or fines imposed on enterprises
that are not in accordance with existing regulations must be
stopped, the circular says.
</P>
<P>
It says that departments and individuals should report any case of
this kinds of illegal activities, and a supervisory system will
be set up to deal with the issue. In addition, news media should
expose serious cases to the public. 
</P>
</TEXT>
