<HEADLINE> China's Electronic Industry Keeping Up Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China's electronic industry in the
first six months of this year had a 26.5 percent increase in
output value over the same period last year, according to recent
statistics from the Ministry of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
The industry's output value amounted to 162.6 billion yuan
during that period.
</P>
<P>
Pre-tax profits in the first half reached 7.2 billion yuan, a
rise of 27.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The production-to-sales ratio of electronic products improved
during the period. Major products like program-controlled
switches, personal computers, and color TV sets all posted
remarkable growth.
</P>
<P>
During that time, China produced 650,000 computers and 10.44
million color TV sets.
</P>
<P>
Also, according to the General Administration of Customs,
imports and exports of electronic products topped 1.1 billion US
dollars worth in the first half year, up 24 percent. 
</P>
