<HEADLINE> Chinese, ASEAN Foreign Ministers Meet in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's peace is hard-won and
thus differences and contradictions should be resolved through
peaceful means, Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian made the remarks this afternoon in a meeting with a
delegation of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN),
including foreign ministers Ali Alatas of Indonesia, Domingo
Siazon of the Philippines and Prachuab Chaiyasarn of Thailand, who
are here to meet Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to them, Qian said not long ago he met with
some ASEAN counterparts during celebration activities for the
return of Hong Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
A few days later, he will again meet them in a meeting of the
ASEAN forum, Qian said, adding frequent contacts between China and
the ASEAN countries are conducive to the progress of the bilateral
friendly relations and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The three foreign ministers agreed with Qian on this, saying
they expected to meet Qian again in Kuala Lumpur later this month.
</P>
<P>
Briefing Qian on the ASEAN's viewpoints on the latest
developments in Cambodia, the ministers said the ASEAN countries
are not willing to see chaos caused by war in Cambodia again. They
hoped Cambodia's internal problems will be solved through peaceful
means at an early date.
</P>
<P>
The ministers noted that the ASEAN will continue to respect
Sihanouk and the form of the Cambodian government and stick to the
principle of not interfering into Cambodia's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
The three foreign ministers also stated that the ASEAN is
willing to strengthen consultations and contacts with various
concerned parties and make due efforts for a peaceful resolution
to the problems in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Qian stressed that as Cambodia's peace is hard-won, no
bleed-shedding and conflicts should occur in Cambodia, and
differences and contradictions should be solved through peaceful
means.
</P>
<P>
China respects the status and role of Cambodian King Sihanouk,
and stands for safeguarding his authority and dignity, and
upholding the current form of the Cambodian government, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, "What has happened in Cambodia belongs to internal
affairs. We hope various parties concerned follow the guideline of
national reconciliation advocated by Sihanouk, restore tranquility
as soon as possible, and make concerted efforts for peace,
stability and development in the country."
</P>
<P>
Qian expressed his appreciation for the ASEAN's efforts for a
peaceful solution to the Cambodian issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
