<HEADLINE> Cancer, Second Largest Killer in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Cancer has become the second largest
 killer in Macao, resulting in 25.6 percent of all deaths in 1996
following top killer cardio- and cerebro-vascular diseases.
</P>
<P>
The latest official statistics show that 362 people died of
cancer last year, accounting for 25.62 percent of all casualties
caused by diseases and poisoning.
</P>
<P>
Diseases related to the circulation system remained the top
killer, with 517 deaths, accounting for 36.59 percent of all.
</P>
<P>
Other top killing diseases in Macao include those with
respiratory system, injuries and poisoning, and those with
digestive system.
</P>
<P>
A group of cancer patients has urged the government to pay more
attention to the rising number of patients, especially those with
epipharynx cancer, and take greater care of those at the terminal
stage.
</P>
<P>
Macao now has two hospitals, one public and one private. The
government said it plans to build a third one on one of Macao's
two islands, which incorporates departments for the mentally-ill
and for patients with terminal diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
