<HEADLINE> Russian Space Station Mir Loses Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Russia's aging space station Mir
today lost all power on most of the craft when the crew
accidentally disconnected a vital cable, but the three astronauts
on board remained safe.
</P>
<P>
The crew, two Russians and an American, said they were thrown
into darkness for one and a half hours and nothing was functioning
on board for the 45 minutes when the Earth obscured the craft from
the sun.
</P>
<P>
The crew communicated with Mission Control from an escape
capsule, which has systems independent from the rest of the Mir.
</P>
