<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Situation in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China today expressed its "sincere
hope" that the parties concerned in Cambodia should cherish the
peaceful situation that had been hard won, and settle their
differences through peaceful means from a perspective of its
national interests so as to prevent the situation from further
deteriorating.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang made this remark when
asked to comment on the current situation in Cambodia at a routine
news briefing here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is concerned about the current situation in
Cambodia, and it holds that Cambodia is a sovereign state and that
those matters which have occurred in Cambodia at present belong to
the country's own internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
"Any actions of other countries should be conducive to the
settlement of differences through peaceful means by all parties
concerned in Cambodia," Tang said.  
</P>
