<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises Making Headway in Central China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises in China's
most populous province of Henan are making greater contributions
to local economic growth and farmers' pockets.
</P>
<P>
The sector produced nearly 477 billion yuan in sales and 5.07
billion yuan in profit in 1996, rising ten-fold and 3.1-fold the
figure of 1990, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises contributed 60 percent to Henan's
industrial output increases, 50 percent to GNP increases and 42.5
percent to farmers' added incomes in the same period.
</P>
<P>
The province has begun to introduce share-holding reform to its
township enterprises in an effort to upgrade them. And 11,000
township enterprises have adopted the stock system, accounting for
15.3 percent of the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Some large township enterprises were selected to operate under
the modern enterprise system, which is widely used among China's
state firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
