<HEADLINE> Nanjing Sees More Laundromats </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Over 30 newly-opened laundromats
in Nanjing have freed many local families of the chore of washing
their own clothes.
</P>
<P>
Most Chinese people traditionally do their own washing, but the
fast tempo of modern-day life has introduced the laundering
service into Chinese society.
</P>
<P>
Wang Ping, assistant general manager of a chain laundromat
company, said that most of their customers are college students,
bachelors and young couples. The cost for a load of clothes is
only about seven yuan (84 US cents). Customers can operate the
machines on their own, or get the laundromat workers to do it for
them.
</P>
<P>
Young people in particular like the laundromats, which liberate
them from household tasks.
</P>
<P>
"This price is acceptable," said Zhang Naining, a junior from
Nanjing Normal University. "I come to the laundromat once or twice
a week," he said.
</P>
<P>
Some store owners said they receive an average of 30 to 40
customers every day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
