<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Declines in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Labor Secretary Leonardo
Quisumbing said here today that the unemployment rate in the
country has been declining during the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He said data of the Department of Labor and Employment showed
that the unemployment rate went down from 8.8 percent in January
1995 to 8.3 percent and 7.7 percent in 1996 and 1997 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Quisumbing added that the improvement in employment coincided
with a rapid growth of the country's labor force, which rose
markedly from 27.85 million in 1994 to the current 31.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The data showed that the increase of employment in rural areas
was the highest as about 47 percent of the country's labor force
found jobs in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
The figures also indicated that more and more Filipinos are now
engaged in better and more productive jobs, especially in the
rural areas, Quisumbing said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
