<HEADLINE> Philippine Defense Minister Favors Talks with Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Defense Secretary Renato
de Villa said today that he favored holding peace talks as the
final and best solution to the government's rift with Muslim
rebels.
</P>
<P>
While stressing that the military has enough capability to deal
with the Moro Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rebels in the
southern part of the country, De Villa said using force is not the
only way to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
"Unlike in a conventional war, you don't really totally
eliminate an enemy force," he said, adding that in an insurgency
situation, people do not use only force, but use many other means
including peace talks to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
"To me, it (holding peace talks) is the best option. To me, it
is the final option. To me, it is an acceptable option to all of
our people because we are all Filipinos here trying to settle our
own problems", he said.
</P>
<P>
The 12,000-member MILF is a breakaway faction of the Moro
National Liberation Front which signed a final peace agreement
with the government last year.
</P>
<P>
The government and the MILF have been trying to re-open their
peace talks stalled by the military's recent offensives in which
dozens of MILF rebels were killed.
</P>
<P>
MILF leaders have warned of a long deadlock in the peace talks,
citing the government's refusal to pull troops out of areas of
conflicting in Cotabato and Maguindanao provinces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
