<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania's Population Drops in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Romania's population fell by
74,000 to 22,585,000 last year due to falling birth rate and
rising death rate.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the nation's birth rate fell to 10.2 per thousand
people while the death rate was up to 12.7 per thousand residents.
</P>
<P>
The number of births in the year decreased by 53,000 while the
number of deaths rose by 14,500, said the Romanian National
Commission of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
In the past seven years, Romania's population declined by
270,000 due to falling birth rate and rising death rate as well as
massive emigration in 1990-1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
