<HEADLINE> Summer Grain Purchase Going on Well in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in the suburban areas of
Shanghai are satisfied with the grain purchase price set by the
Shanghai municipal government this summer, said Ye Jiaqi, an
official of the Municipal Grain Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Ye also said that to encourage grain production, his bureau set
the grain purchase price in Shanghai higher than in its
neighboring provinces and cities, and gave subsidies to farmers
who sell rape seeds, wheat and barley to the government.
