<HEADLINE> Iranian Minister Says Afghan Northern Faction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister
Alauddin Broujerdi said today that he had found Afghanistan's
northern opposition alliance willing to seek peace with the
Islamic militia Taliban.
</P>
<P>
"I have found a spirit for peace during my several visits to
northern Afghanistan," Broujerdi told newsmen upon arrival at
Islamabad airport.
</P>
<P>
"The pre-requisite for peace is that all parties should show
willingness for peace and should not opt for military solution,"
