<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EBRD Supports Bulgarian Bank Privatization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The board of directors of the
European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD) today
decided to support the privatization project for the United
Bulgarian Bank (UBB), the Bank Consolidation Company (BCC) said.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD Co-director of Financial Institutions, Pierre
Mellinger, is expected to arrive early next week from the bank's
headquarters in London to sign the deal in which the EBRD will buy
a 35 per cent interest in UBB, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
With the sale of the UBB, Bulgaria fulfils one of its main
commitments on the agreement with International Monetary Fund,
that Bulgaria would privatize two state-owned banks by
September. The U.S. investment company, Oppenheimer and Co., will
acquire 30 percent of UBB and the state-owned Bulbank will retain
a 35 percent stake.
</P>
<P>
The EBRD recently said it would support the development of the
private sector in Bulgaria and take part in privatization as a
mediator and through direct financing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
