<HEADLINE> Training Center for Intellectual Property Right Founded in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Intellectual Property
Rights Training Center was recently founded in China's largest
trade and financial city to improve the country's investment
environment.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Shanghai Patent Trademark Office, the largest
patent trademark agency in China, the center is open to attorneys
and personnel from foreign enterprises and companies.
</P>
<P>
It aims to inform them of Chinese laws and regulations about
intellectual property rights, including patent law, trademark law
and copyright law, so that they can use these laws and regulations
to protect their companies' property rights in China.
</P>
<P>
Experts from different universities and the Patent Office of
the People's Republic of China will be invited to give lectures.
</P>
<P>
The first session of the center, to be held in October, will
enroll English-speaking students from the United States, Germany,
Japan and other countries. Classes in other languages will be
offered in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
