<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises Thriving in Liaoning Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises have now
become a driving force behind economic growth in northeast China's
Liaoning Province, a traditional base of State industries.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the introduction of the market economic system, an
increasing number of state enterprises in the province flounder
against the fierce competition. In contrast, township businesses
are thriving due to their flexible managerial system.
</P>
<P>
Last year, local township undertakings generated more than 420
billion yuan in output value and earned 25 billion yuan in net
profits, and paid nearly five billion yuan in taxes to the
government. The businesses also provided five million jobs for the
local surplus laborers.
</P>
<P>
Most township enterprises are concentrated in the provincial
capital of Shenyang and the coastal city of Dalian. The are mostly
involved in the fields of machinery, light industry, building
materials, and chemicals, and account for more than three-fourths
of the local total large businesses in the sectors.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 80 township enterprise groups and more
than 300 medium- and large-sized township enterprises. The number
of such enterprises is expected to climb to 800 by the turn of the
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
