<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dongguan Becomes Major Farm Produce Exporter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 17 (Xinhua) -- Dongguan, one of the four
dynamic economic areas in south China's Guangdong Province, has
turned into a leading farm produce exporter in Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
On the strength of its next-door location to Hong Kong and
Macao, Dongguan has promoted poultry, aquatic products, fruit and
flower exports to other countries. Its exports from agriculture
last year surpassed 100 million US dollars last year, doubling the
1990 figure.
</P>
<P>
As Dongguan is an industrialized area with limited amount of
arable land, the local government has devoted great efforts to
develop high-efficiency, high-quality and high-yield agriculture,
build grain, vegetable and fruit transit stations and explore
the overseas market.
</P>
<P>
It has set up 140 foreign-funded agricultural firms which
export their own products while purchasing goods from
individually-run firms or private companies, then export them
through their worldwide marekting channels.
</P>
<P>
State-run foreign trade departments have played a leading role
in foreign trade. The Dongguan Foodstuff Import and Export Company
alone exports 20 million US dollars-worth of farm and sideline
products each year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
