<HEADLINE> 800 Kilograms of Narcotic Drugs Burned in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 17 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities set ablaze
in the last two days a total of 824.19 kilograms of narcotic drugs
seized in Kokang area, northern Shan state of the country, The New
Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The ceremonial destruction, which took place in Laukkai area in
the same state on Tuesday, was the seventh time made on those
confiscated from opium refineries and traffickers in the Kokang
area by the army units and law enforcement bodies.
</P>
<P>
The narcotic drugs burned include 783.13 kilograms of opium,
21.33 kilograms of heroin and other chemicals such as morphine,
ether, ammonium chloride and paraphernalia, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Kokang area was the place where the first destruction of
seized narcotic drugs in Myanmar was initiated.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1996, a total of 4,840.15 kilograms of narcotic
drugs, precursor chemicals and paraphernalia were burned in the
area with 11 opium refineries and 1,782 hectares of poppy
cultivation destroyed, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities destroyed 24 heroin refineries in the
entire country in 1996 and the first three months of 1997,
according to Myanmar drug control sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
