largest export sector since 1995.
</P>
<P>
last year, exports of machinery and electronics grew 9.9 percent
to 48 billion US dollars. But high-tech products and equipment
accounted for only about ten percent of the total machinery and
electronics exports, compared with 40 percent in developed
nations, the paper said.  
