<HEADLINE> Azerbaijan's Economy Takes Favorable Turn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Azerbaijan's economy has taken a
favourable turn in the first half of this year with a 5.2 percent
increase in the gross domestic product (GDP) compared to the same
period last year, says the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
Vdhed Ahyndov, the state adviser of economic policy, told a
news conference in Baku, the capital of Azerbaijan, that the
national economic situation was sound with increases showing up in
all products, including machine building and in the metallurgical
industry.
</P>
<P>
The foreign trade situation improved greatly during the first
five months of this year, while the budget deficit accounted for
1.6 percent of GDP, Ahyndov told the reporters.
</P>
<P>
The trade surplus reached 53 million U.S. dollars in the half
year, compared with the trade deficit of 150 million dollars last
year.
</P>
<P>
Share holding in industrial enterprises and reform of the
private process were accelerated by a big margin because of a
sharp increase in investment. The real income of residents
increased by 35 percent against the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Located south of the Caucasus, Azerbaijan is a state of the
Commonwealth of Independent States. The output of the country
showed the first increase last year with a 1.3 percent GDP
increase. 
</P>
</TEXT>
