<HEADLINE> Peruvian Foreign Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
LIMA, July 16 (Xinhua) - Peruvian Foreign Minister
Francisco Tudela resigned today, according to a statement from
Presidential press office.
</P>
<P>
President Alberto Fujimori accepted the resignation and
replaced him with Eduardo Ferrero Costa, a foreign affairs
specialist.
</P>
<P>
Tudela, 41, was held hostage by Marxist guerrillas for four
months in the Japanese embassy in Lima with 71 other VIPs. He
was wounded when troops stormed the house on April 22.
</P>
<P>
Tudela's departure came as Fujimori faced a storm of media
outrage over a phone-tapping scandal and the annulment of an
Israeli-born businessman's citizenship. 
</P>
