<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Homicides Increase in America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The homicide rate has jumped
spectacularly in the American continents in the past decade, the
Costa Rican Planning Ministry says.
</P>
<P>
Although the rate has dropped in Mexico, Costa Rica and
Paraguay, the homicide figures have shot up in all of the other
countries, said the ministry quoting a World Bank report.
</P>
<P>
There were 20.5 homicides for every 100,000 inhabitants in
Colombia in the 1970s-1980s, but the rate was up to 89.5 in the
1980s-1990s.
</P>
<P>
Following Colombia was Brazil where the rate rose from 11.5 to
19.7 over the same periods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
