<HEADLINE> Tebbutt Reaches Third Round at Washington Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Aussie Michael Tebbuttwon
advanced to the third round of the 675,000 U.S. dollars Washington
Classic with a 6-3, 6-3 win over fourth-seeded American Chris
Woodruff on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The win was his second in as many days after a long frustrating
run since last year's U.S. Open.
</P>
<P>
Tebbutt then joined compatriots Jason Stoltenberg, Luke Smith
and Scott Draper in final 16. Three of them will next play
U.S. rivals.
</P>
<P>
Tebbutt will take on Vince Spadea while fifth seed Stoltenberg
meets David Wheaton and seventh seed Draper takes on Steve
Campbell. Smith plays New Zealand's Brett Steven.
</P>
<P>
Tebbutt, who squeezed into top 100 in 1985, has slid to 271st
and played only three ATP matches this year. He served eight aces
and won 23 of 25 first-serve points to oust 56th-ranked Woodruff.
</P>
