<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State polyurethane Sector Seeks Foreign Partners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 17 (Xinhua) -- China and foreign chemical
companies plan to develop China's polyurethane sector to meet
demand in the mainland's auto and electric appliance market,
today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
Polyurethane, a synthetic resin, is used in elastic components
of motor vehicles, packages, building materials and as insulation
foam in refrigerators. It can also be used to make synthetic fibre
and rubber.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China produced 445,000 tons of polyurethane, nearly
five times the amount in 1989. The production of polyurethane
worldwide was 6.5 million tons, up 3 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Xu Guide, director of China Polyurethane
Industry Assn as saying that the total volume of products in China
made from polyurethane will reach roughly 700,000 tons a year by
the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
But lack of money in the polyurethane sector is forcing domestic
polyurethane makers to seek foreign partners.
</P>
<P>
The US-based Dow Chemical Co. and Britain-based Imperial
Chemical Inc. have already invested in China. Other prospective
investors include BASF and Bayer of Germany, Ancro Chemical of the
US, and Shell of Holland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
