<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Pozdniakov Crowned in Fencing Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Russia's Stanislaw
Pozdniakov, who won the sabre gold at last year's Olympic Games,
beat Italy's Luigi Tarantino 15-12 to win the title in the World
Fencing Championships in Cape Town on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tarantino, ranked 15th in the world, had defeated Olympic
bronze medallist and world number two Damien Touya of France in
his semifinal but fell just short against the world's top-ranked
sabre man.
</P>
<P>
In the men's foil, Ukraine's Sergei Golubitsky triumphed over
Kim Young-ho of South Korea in a tense final.
</P>
<P>
Golubitsky surged into an 11-3 lead and Kim levelled at 11-11
before the Ukrainian triumphed 15-14. 
</P>
