<HEADLINE> Habsudova Secures Quarter Spot in Czech Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Karina Habsudova of Slovakia
secured her quarterfinal berth as her opponent crumpled in the
decider at the Czech Open ladies' clay court tennis tournament on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The third-seeded Habsudova lost the first of the second-round
match 4-6, outplayed Diaz-Oliva 6-2 in the second. She was leading
4-0 in the third set when Diaz-Oliva crumpled.
</P>
<P>
WTA physician Kirsten Patton said Diaz-Oliva who had health
problems before the match, collapsed from exhaustion during the
play.
</P>
<P>
Marion Maruska of Austria also advanced to the quarterfinals
after Laurence Courtois of Belgium retired because of stomach
problems.
</P>
<P>
Romania's Catalina Cristea beat Rene Simpson of Canada in two
straight sets 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the last second-round match of the day, the Czech Republic's
Ludmila Richterova was leading over second-seeded Ruxandra
Dragomir of Romania 7-6 (11-9), 3-2, when the play was interrupted
for rain.
</P>
<P>
That match, as well as the remaining second-round matches, will
be played on Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
