<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dry Spell Lingers in Hebei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 17 (Xinhua) -- A serious drought has been
continuing since early June in north China's Hebei Province,
damaging crops and causing a shortage of drinking water.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said 3.05 million hectares, or half of the
province's farmland, are suffering from the drought which now has
irreparably damaged 48,000 hectares of crops.
</P>
<P>
The dry spell makes it impossible for farmers to do summer
sowing, worse still, some 340,000 people now have difficulty
finding drinking water.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government is mobilizing all kinds of resources
to fight the drought as there is little hope of adequate rainfall
in the near future to ease the situation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
