<HEADLINE> Two More Attacks on Foreign Personnel Occur in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, July 16 (Xinhua)-- An attack on a U.S. soldier and an
explosion outside a UN police office occorred on early Wednesday
morning as the latest of a series of incidents against foreign
personnel following NATO's operation of arresting war crime
indictees.
</P>
<P>
According to the NATO-led Stabilization Force (SFOR), the
American soldier was stabbed from behind by an unidentified man
with a sickle and sustained a two to three inch cut on his
shoulder.
</P>
<P>
SFOR said that local police and SFOR were investigating the
incident which took place in the Serb-controlled Kladaji area in
northern Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a grenade exploded near the office of the UN
International Police Task Force in the north Bosnian town of
Prijedor, where NATO special forces killed one war crime suspect
and arrested another on last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, in which a car was slightly damaged, was the
third in three days since Sunday. The other two blasts in
Zvornik and Banja Luka respectively destroyed a car belonging
the Organization of Security and Cooperation in Europe and
shattered windows of the residence of OSCE employee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
