<HEADLINE> Dow Surpasses 8,000 Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
pierced through 8,000 points today as a flood of more good news on
company profits, inflation and interest rates came out.
</P>
<P>
On Wall Street, the Dow rose by 63.17 to 8,038.88. The Dow has
already gained more than 1,500 points, or about 24 percent this
year, more than twice what most experts had predicted for all of
1997. By closing above 8,000, the famed market measure has now
doubled from 4,000 in less than 2 years and a half.
</P>
<P>
Other popular market measures also pushed further into record
territory as interest rates sank to their lowest level since
December in the bond market after the Labor Department reported
that consumer prices inched only 0.1 percent higher last month,
holding the inflation rate for the first half of the year to just
1.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index posted its biggest one-day point
gain ever, rising 38.52, or 2.5 percent, to 1,580.63. Over the
past 10 sessions, the Nasdaq has risen 142.38 points, or nearly 10
percent.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by more than a 2-to-1
margin on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 646.00
million shares, the fifth busiest day in the exchange's history.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 10.80 to 936.56, the
NYSE composite index rose 4.25 to 485.24, and the American Stock
Exchange composite index rose 3.08 to 638.03.
</P>
<P>
The second-quarter company earnings have turned better. The
biggest earnings news came late Tuesday from Intel, whose
better-than-expected results energized the technology sector today
and boosted the Nasdaq composite index to its 10th straight record
high.  
</P>
</TEXT>
