<HEADLINE> IDB Assists Peru to Fight Plant and Animal Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 16 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 45.6 million U.S.
dollar loan to Peru to help financing programs to control and
reduce animal and plant diseases.
</P>
<P>
The program is designed to eventually assure the inspection of
100 percent of imported farm products. New agricultural
checkpoints will be built at airports and seaports, specialized
personnel will be trained, and a national pesticides commission
will be established.
</P>
<P>
Two national laboratories that identify agricultural health
problems will be upgraded, and several specific projects will be
undertaken to control and eradicate specific pests and diseases,
such as the fruitfly and foot-an-mouth disease.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the program is some 76 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
